item.title: First Bewick's swan's flight to the Arctic signals the arrival of spring as birds return to Russia t
item.description: THE first Bewick’s swan of the season has set off for the Arctic, signalling spring is near in the UK. Leho arrived at the Wildfowl and Wetlands Trust in Wisbech, Cambs, in December but begun the 1,500-mile trip to Russia for his summer roost at 7am yesterday. The tracked bird was in Germany by the afternoon. The swans shelter here over winter but return to Russia to breed. At this stage of the year, swans begin preparing for the tough journey ahead by resting, feeding and making practice runs.
